# Vite / GitHub Pages

Pages URL: `https://fogrexon.github.io/cursor-workspace/`. Missing `base` → asset 404s.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig({
  base: '/cursor-workspace/<app-name>/', // trailing slash required
  build: {
    outDir: '../../docs/<app-name>',
    emptyOutDir: true,
  },
});
```

- No root-absolute asset links (`/foo.png`). Use `import`, relative paths, or `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`
- SPA routers: pass base (e.g. React Router `basename={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`); prefer hash routing to avoid Pages 404s
- After build, confirm `docs/<app-name>/index.html` paths start with `/cursor-workspace/<app-name>/`

## Local libs (`file:`)

```json
{ "dependencies": { "@playground/theme": "file:../../lib/theme" } }
```

Lib `package.json` needs `name` (`@playground/…`), `main`/`exports`. After lib changes, re-`npm install` in consumers.
